HEADWORD: Hypermetamorphosis
<hw>Hy`per*met`a*mor"pho*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hyper-</ets> + <ets>metamorphosis</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A kind of metamorphosis, in certain insects, in
which the larva itself undergoes remarkable changes of form and
structure during its growth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hypermeter</ent>⟦br⟧
